text: As shown in Fig . 4c , the proteins involved in the stimulus - response were enriched , and most of them are reported to respond to viral infection . These proteins can be potential targets for controlling viral infection . Dynamic changes in the expressed proteins in cluster B were noted . They were initially down - regulated at 12 and 24 hpi , followed by a rapid return to near basal levels at 36 hpi and slight up - regulation at 48 and 60 hpi . Thus , 12 and 24 hpi were the best time points to study these proteins ( Fig . 4 ) .
